709579f-a.text:
Sixth Ave., west side, north from West 54th to 56th Streets, showing mainly Loew's Ziegfield Theatre (Motion Picture) at the N.W. corner of West 54th Street. This structure erected by Florenz Ziegfield to house his "Follies" was converted for motion picture exhibition subsequent to his demise. This set of same, consists of a negative and a positive.
September 1935.
W.P.A. Photo.

709578f-a.text:
Sixth Avenue, east side, south from W. 54th Street. Towering structures are units of Rockefeller Center. Under construction is the 70 story R. C. A. Building. It's slightly smaller component is the R. K. O. Building.
Note the old 6th Avenue "E1" bend at 53rd Street. This is absent in the later view. The streetcar tracks
are gone and the surface repaved.
View 1: September 11, 1932
View 2: April 20, 1939
P. L. Sperr
